14/11/2002
TIRANA, Albania -- On Wednesday (13 November), Council of Europe (CoE) Parliamentary Assembly co-rapporteurs praised judicial reforms undertaken by the Albanian government. 
Polish and Danish deputies Jerzy Smorawinski and Soeren Soendergaard, members of the CoE Parliamentary Assembly Monitoring Commission, arrived in Tirana at the beginning of the week to prepare a report on implementation of the obligations and commitments undertaken by Albania. 
Meeting with Socialist Party Secretary General Gramoz Ruci, they expressed satisfaction with improved efforts against corruption and illegal trafficking. 
(BBC Monitoring, ATA - 13/11/02)
